<DOC><DOCNO> AP881208-0165 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-08-88 1618EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a AM-People     12-08 0673</FIRST><SECOND>AM-People,0700</SECOND><HEAD>People in the News</HEAD><HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Six-year-old Prince William is learning to ski onthe slope where Britain's Olympic loser, Eddie ``the Eagle''Edwards, made his first faltering leap to fame, the manager of theski center said Thursday.   William has taken three lessons on the dry ski slope at theGloucester Ski Center near Highgrove, his family's country home westof London, said Dave Watson.   William is second in line to the British throne behind hisfather, Prince Charles.   Charles and his wife, Princess Diana, are accomplished skiiers,and Diana recently disclosed her older son ``loves skiing.''   Edwards soared to fame in the Winter Olympics by finishing lastin two ski jumping events. Fans fell in love with his thick glasses,jutting chin and unflappable humor.</TEXT><DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Actor Gary Busey, recovering from headinjuries suffered in a motorcycle crash, was out of intensive-careunit as his condition continued to improve.   Busey, 44, who was nominated for an Academy Award for hisstarring role in ``The Buddy Holly Story'' in 1978, hit his head ona curb after being thrown from his Harley Davidson motorcycleSunday. He underwent 90 minutes of brain surgery after the crash.   Busey, a Malibu resident, was moved to a regular hospital roomfrom the intensive-care unit Wednesday at Cedars-Sinai MedicalCenter, where he remained in serious condition, spokesman Ron Wisesaid.   ``He's really far along for somebody who had his kind of brainsurgery only three days ago,'' Wise said.   The actor was expected to make a complete recovery, Wise saidearlier.   Busey, who wasn't wearing a helmet during the crash, hascampaigned against efforts to pass a California law requiring allmotorcycle riders and passengers to wear helmets.   Lt. Ellis Smith said a helmet probably would have protected Buseyfrom head injury, adding, ``I don't think even the helmet would havebeen broken.''</TEXT><DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Prince Harry came to the rescue Thursday when a shyco-star forgot her lines in their kindergarten Nativity play.   The 4-year-old son of Prince Charles and Princess Diana wasplaying a shepherd and had just uttered his lines ``in a veryconfident voice'' when a classmate playing another shepherd forgothers, said a Buckingham Palace spokesman who was in the audience.   The prince stepped closer, whispered the forgotten lines into herear, and the show went on, said the spokesman, speaking anonymouslyin keeping with British custom.   Charles, heir to the British throne, and his wife, Diana, were inthe audience for their son's first speaking role. Harry played agoblin in his school play last year, but it was a silent part.</TEXT><DATELINE>MINEOLA, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Matilda Cuomo, wife of Gov. Mario Cuomo, isin a court fight over her father's will.   Mrs. Cuomo and two of her siblings are battling their mother andtwo other brothers over where the will of Charles Raffa will beprobated and who should be the executor of the $13.7 million estate.   A Nassau County Surrogate Court judge set Jan. 5 for a hearing.He also ordered on Wednesday that the temporary executor, Sam Raffa,one of the three sons, not dispose of any property.   Raffa claims he was named executor in a will codicil made in 1984shortly after his father was severely beaten during a mugging.Charles Raffa never recovered and died Oct. 19, 1988.   Sam Raffa also wants the will probated in Nassau County. Hismother, Mary, and brother, Frank, have sided with him.   Matilda Cuomo, along with her sister Nancy Mazzola and brother,Joseph, want to use an executor named in a 1977 will. They want thewill validated in Brooklyn, where they said their father lived mostof his life.   ``This is not a split in the family,'' Mrs. Mazzola said. ``We'rejust trying to make some decisions.''   But Sam Raffa said in a court affidavit that trying to remove himas executor was ``part of a plan to eventually attack the provisionsof my father's will.''</TEXT></DOC>